column2: 1. Plan and pack appropriately especially food, water, first aid kit, clothing. 2. Don’t hike at dawn or dusk 3. Make low level noise to avoid wild animals e.g. bears, rattle snakes. 4. Stay on paths until you get to a sampling site. 5. Be aware of dangers & how to avoid e.g. Giardia, poison oak, ticks. 6. Keep emergency numbers handy 7. Leave no trace.
